WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.560
Welcome to the test set. Here we talk with some of the brightest thinkers and tinkerers

00:00:06.560 --> 00:00:11.480
in statistical analysis, scientific computing, and machine learning. Digging into what makes

00:00:11.480 --> 00:00:16.760
them tick, plus the insights, experiments, and OMG moments that shape the field.

00:00:16.760 --> 00:00:21.799
On this episode, we sit down with Paige Bailey, DevRel Engineering Lead at Google ThemeLine.

00:00:21.799 --> 00:00:26.200
She started out coding text-based games from Byte Magazine onto her Apple II computer,

00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:31.719
which is a real throwback. Her website mentions she makes weird things digitally in IRL, like

00:00:31.719 --> 00:00:37.959
a bot that emails her, roasting her taste in music, or solar-powered, silent-film birdhouses

00:00:37.959 --> 00:00:43.160
as street art in San Francisco. She runs us through her background in geophysics, where

00:00:43.160 --> 00:00:47.759
she was introduced to Python and open source early. She discusses how she weaves a variety

00:00:47.759 --> 00:00:53.680
of Google APIs and services together to make things fun, weird, and educational.

00:00:53.680 --> 00:00:57.840
And I left feeling like my use of AI could be so much weirder, so I'm so excited for

00:00:57.840 --> 00:00:59.680
people to listen to this interview.

00:00:59.680 --> 00:01:04.440
Paige Bailey, welcome to the test set.

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:06.120
Awesome. Thank you for having me.

00:01:06.120 --> 00:01:10.599
Yeah. So we were here in San Francisco, and you mentioned you took a Waymo in, which seems

00:01:10.599 --> 00:01:11.599
very relevant.

00:01:11.599 --> 00:01:13.040
I did. It is very on-brand, yes.

00:01:13.040 --> 00:01:19.080
I love that. Just by way of introduction, so you're a Developer Relations Engineering

00:01:19.080 --> 00:01:20.879
Lead at Google DeepMind?

00:01:20.879 --> 00:01:21.879
Correct.

00:01:22.080 --> 00:01:27.639
I've had an incredible career of doing a lot of things, which I really want to get to.

00:01:27.639 --> 00:01:34.239
Because I always forget, I want to make sure to say, I'm Michael Chao, the host. And I'm

00:01:34.239 --> 00:01:40.400
joined by Hadley Wickham, Chief Scientist at Posit, and Isabel Zimmerman, credible Posit

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:50.360
software engineer. And we're so happy to have you on here in beautiful San Francisco.

